The paper deals with machine learning techniques, specifically imputation methods and classification algorithms, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data mining (cs.DM). The use of genetic programming to search for the optimal combination of these techniques falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the application of these techniques to classification problems with missing data can also be considered under the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
